cs.HC, cs.LG, cs.CY, cs.SI, cs.IR

The paper focuses on developing a visualization system for analyzing and comparing the predictions of sensor-data classifiers. This involves dealing with complex temporal sequences, high prediction frequency, and imprecise labeling, which are common challenges in human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and machine learning (cs.LG). The system also integrates with a version control system, which falls under the category of cybernetics (cs.CY). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of an algebra over track representations to filter, compose, and compare classification outputs, which is related to information retrieval (cs.IR) and signal processing (cs.SI).
